qas.question: What is the main railway station

answers.text: Utrecht Centraal is the main railway station of Utrecht

qas.question: Does the rail station provide 24 hour service

answers.text: Utrecht Centraal is a station on the night service, providing 7 days a week an all night service

qas.question: Are there rail services to Germany

answers.text: International InterCityExpress (ICE) services to Germany (and further) through Arnhem call at Utrecht Centraal

qas.question: where to regular local trains provide service

answers.text: local trains to all areas surrounding Utrecht also depart from Utrecht Centraal; and service several smaller stations

qas.question: What is the main railway station of the Netherlands?
When did the Dutch Railway Museum open?

context: <a0_0><b4_0>Utrecht Centraal<b4_0/> is the main railway station of Utrecht<a0_0/>. There are regular intercity services to all major Dutch cities; direct services to Schiphol Airport. <a1_0>Utrecht Centraal is a station on the night service, providing 7 days a week an all night service<a1_0/> to (among others) Schiphol Airport, Amsterdam and Rotterdam. <a2_0>International InterCityExpress (ICE) services to Germany (and further) through Arnhem call at Utrecht Centraal<a2_0/>. Regular <a3_0>local trains to all areas surrounding Utrecht also depart from Utrecht Centraal; and service several smaller stations<a3_0/>: Utrecht Lunetten, Utrecht Vaartsche Rijn, Utrecht Overvecht, Utrecht Leidsche Rijn, Utrecht Terwijde, Utrecht Zuilen and Vleuten. A former station <b6_0>Utrecht Maliebaan<b6_0/> closed in <b5_0>1939<b5_0/> and has since been converted into the Dutch Railway Museum.
